cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.HC

The paper discusses the state of the art in predictive models of student success in MOOCs, which involves machine learning and data analysis techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CY (Computers and Society), as the paper also discusses the implications of such models for personalized learning and adaptive interventions. The paper also involves natural language processing techniques for feature engineering, which suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of student models, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
